The structural composition of the produced Cu and CuO NPs was recognized from XRD pattern presented in Fig. 4(a). Bragg reflections at 2θ values 43.047°, 50.189°, and 73.910° characterize the crystallographic planes (111), (200), and (220) of cubic structure of copper (JCPDS card no. 85-1326). XRD patterns for CuO NPs validated its high purity according to the standard card (JCPDS 48-1548). According to the strong peaks in the XRD patterns, the CuO NPs were crystalline with no impurities. The broadening of the peaks indicates that the average crystal size is small (22 nm), as predicted by peak (111) and (022) using the Scherer formula (Nayak et al., 2019).5D=KλβcosΘ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
